            "highlights": [
                {
                    "text": "The truth was probably that my mother had been so defined by the existence of my father that when he died, she couldn’t see anything else before her",
                    "date": "2025-07-22T16:43:09.751"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The proprietor had never thought of keeping a pet because he thought he’d make a bad owner, but he saw then that not all living things pin all their hopes and dreams on you. Life goes on and it was egotistical to imagine otherwise.",
                    "date": "2025-07-23T05:37:29.463"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Being able to be sad is a form of happiness too.",
                    "date": "2025-07-23T05:43:05.441"
                },
                {
                    "text": "she knew that if she ever tried to paint a face, it would look like Nelly, and she could not afford to see Nelly ever again",
                    "date": "2025-07-23T06:08:17.915"
                }
            ]
        },
